cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper deals with an online learning problem involving contextual cascading bandits, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for this problem and provides theoretical analysis of its performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves clustering, which is a topic in data science, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with online learning, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category.
